> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 162 "As you may
 have noted the addition/subtraction operatios where carried out while
 the multiplication/division operations were just indicated.  The Mapl
e commands  " }{TEXT 264 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 6 " and  " }{TEXT 265 8 
"simplify" }{TEXT -1 298 "  can be used to rearrange and manipulate al
gebraic sums and products of polynomial expressions.  Go back to each \+
of your calculations of a., b., c. and d. and add to each line a comma
nd to expand the calculation and a command to simplify the caclulation
.  E.g.,  the line for a. would change from:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 4 "f*g;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "to " 
}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "f*g; expand(f*g); simplify
(f*g);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
17 "Note the effect  " }{TEXT 268 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }
{TEXT 269 8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 42 "  have on the way the calculation
 appears." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
19 "The Maple commands " }{TEXT 266 16 "expand, simplify" }{TEXT -1 5 
" and " }{TEXT 267 6 "normal" }{TEXT -1 482 " can be use to rearrange,
 manipulate and simplify (cancel common factors) algebraic sums, produ
cts and quotients of rational expressions.   When a rational expressio
n is normalized, any common factors are cancelled.  Go back to each of
 your calculations of e., f., g., h. and i. and add to each line a com
mand to expand the calculation, to normalize the calculation, to simpl
ify the calculation and both expand and normalize the calculation.  E.
g., the line for e. would change from" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "F*H/G;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 2 "to" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "F := \+
x^4-1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"FG,&*$)%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"F
