ave on the way the calculation appears." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "2.  Factoring.  The Maple command  \+
" }{TEXT 275 6 "factor" }{TEXT -1 299 " can be used to factor algebrai
c polynomial expressions and rational expressions.  When rational expr
essions are factors, any common factors are cancelled.  Factor each of
 the polynomials f, g, h, F, G and H.  Also, factor the algebraic and \+
rational expressions a., b., c., d., e., f., g., h. and i." }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 271 "3.  Fundamental \+
Theorem of Algebra.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra asserts that e
very non-constant polynomial (with complex-valued coefficients) has a \+
root (a zero, a solution).  A consequence of the Fundamental Theorem o
f Algebra is that every polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 276 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 13 " has exactly " }{TEXT 277 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 108 " roots.  A
n alternate formulation of this consequence would be that every non-co
nstant polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 279 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 38 " can be f
actored into a product of a  " }{TEXT 278 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 16 " linear \+
factors." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
35 "Consider the following polynomials:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "I.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "f := x^3-x^2-
2*x" "6#>%\"fG,(*$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*$F'\"\"#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT 
-1 15 "         II.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "g := 6*x^3+11*x^2+6*x+1" "6#>%
\"gG,**&\"\"'\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"$F(F(*&\"#6F(*$F*\"\"#F(F(*&F'F(F*F(F(F(
F(" }{TEXT -1 24 "                 III.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "h := x^3-5
*x+x^2-5;" "6#>%\"hG,**$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*&\"\"&F)F'F)!\"\"*$F'\"\"#F)F
+F," }{TEXT -1 19 "                   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "
IV.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "F := x^4-144" "6#>%\"FG,&*$%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"\"
$W\"!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 19 "             V.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "G := 3*x
^4+4*x^3-2*x^2+x-6;" "6#>%\"GG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"%F(F(*&F+F(*$F
*F'F(F(*&\"\"#F(*$F*F/F(!\"\"F*F(\"\"'F1" }{TEXT -1 15 "         VI.  \+
 " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "H := x^5-x^2-2*x" "6#>%\"HG,(*$%\"xG\"\"&\"\"\"*$F'
\"\"#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 24 "                        " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 172 "Factor
 each polynomial and determine whether Maple was able to find enough l
inear factors to demonstrate the above assertion about the appropriate
 number of linear factors." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 " f := x^3-x^2-2*x;" }}{PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"fG,(*$)%
\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"F**$)F(\"\"#F*!\"\"*&F-F*F(F*F." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(f);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#
*(%\"xG\"\"\",&F$F%F%F%F%,&F$F%\"\"#!\"\"F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 67 "Maple did find three linear factors for this third degr
ee plynomial" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "g := 6*x^3+
